<h1>Operation Absolute Resolve: How the US Captured Nicolás Maduro</h1>
<div class="byline">Updated March 2026 · Data: Wikipedia, NBC News, CNN, AS/COA, Airwars, Just Security</div>

<div class="story-body">
  <p>On January 3, 2026, US Delta Force soldiers and FBI agents stormed a fortified compound in Caracas and seized Venezuelan President Nicolás Maduro — the most audacious American military operation in decades. By dawn, he was aboard the USS Iwo Jima. By evening, he was in a Brooklyn jail.</p>
  <p>The raid was the culmination of a months-long pressure campaign that began with naval deployments, escalated through dozens of lethal boat strikes in the Caribbean and Pacific, and ended with the first US strike inside Venezuelan territory just days before the final operation.</p>
</div>

