<div class="source-note">
  <strong>Note:</strong> The US did not release public evidence confirming drugs aboard struck vessels in most cases. Human rights organizations and UN experts condemned the strikes as violations of international law. Legal scholars questioned the executive's authority to conduct them without congressional authorization.
</div>

<div class="story-body">
  <p>The operation — named <em>Operation Absolute Resolve</em> — launched at 10:46 PM ET on January 2. Helicopters flew at 100 feet above water into Venezuelan airspace. Venezuelan forces opened fire; one US aircraft was hit but remained airborne. Maduro attempted to flee to a steel-reinforced safe room he'd had built for exactly this scenario. He gave up.</p>
  <p>A CIA team had been inside Venezuela since August 2025, tracking his movements, meals, and even his pets. Delta Force trained for months using a replica of his compound. Trump had personally called Maduro days earlier to warn him to surrender. He refused.</p>
</div>

